The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for question answering tasks that involve complex arithmetic and logic reasoning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also proposes a differentiable neural network that can learn to call a small set of basic arithmetic and logic operations, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper uses a synthetic table-comprehension dataset, which suggests that it may also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the limitations of traditional recurrent networks and attentional models, which suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for image recognition, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
